properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 13 at 10:05AM CST until February 14 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Bitter Cold Wind Chills through Tonight...

.Accumulating snow has ended over the area, but strong northwest
winds, blowing snow and bitter cold temperatures will continue
this morning. The bitter cold air will remain over the region
tonight, leading to wind chills as low as 20 to 25 below into
Friday morning.

Many untreated roads this will remain snow and ice covered this
morning due to the overnight snowfall and drifting snow.
Scattered flurries will continue along with pockets of blowing and
drifting snow.

* WHAT...For the Winter Weather Advisory, there will be areas of
blowing and drifting snow this morning. Winds gusting as high
as 35 mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills
expected tonight. Wind chills as low as 25 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of east central, northeast and southeast Iowa.

* WHEN...For the Winter Weather Advisory, until noon CST today.
For the Wind Chill Advisory, until 10 AM CST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous travel conditions will continue through late
this morning. The cold wind chills this morning and overnight could
cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

Call 511 for road conditions.
